1
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,023
Hi, Mom.

2
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,162
Well, if you're calling me that...

3
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:41,542
...then I guess I really must be dying.

4
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,046
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

5
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:53,387
The surgery went well.

6
00:00:54,388 --> 00:00:56,849
You're all right.
You'll be okay.

7
00:00:58,058 --> 00:00:59,726
You're not a very good liar.

8
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:03,605
Just like someone else I know.

9
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:06,233
I'm looking into other hospitals.

10
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:10,112
We'll transfer you,
redo the surgery,

11
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:11,655
with the best doctor.

12
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,032
Stop it.

13
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:18,036
There's no point, really.

14
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:20,372
It's been a miserable life.

15
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:25,460
It's time now.

16
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,713
You should go.

17
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:32,092
So I can rest in peace.

18
00:01:34,011 --> 00:01:36,221
Why does it matter if I'm here?

19
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:41,059
Staying with me will only
make things harder for you.

20
00:01:41,143 --> 00:01:42,603
I know that.

21
00:01:44,188 --> 00:01:46,023
I really hated my life here.

22
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:49,443
And I resented you a lot, too.

23
00:01:52,988 --> 00:01:56,408
It hurt every time you called me
a luckless brat

24
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,911
or told me nothing will ever work out.

25
00:02:00,204 --> 00:02:01,872
Just give up and live with it.

26
00:02:03,874 --> 00:02:05,709
Just hearing you say those things...

27
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,297
...made it impossible to even dream.

28
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,509
But I realized...

29
00:02:14,343 --> 00:02:16,428
...that's just how you had
to live your life.

30
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:21,808
And that's why I ran because
I didn't want to live like you.

31
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:24,603
I thought that maybe...

32
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:28,315
...if I just ran far enough...

33
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,736
...I could find a way out of that long,
dark tunnel.

34
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,825
But no matter how far I ran...

35
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,330
...there was no end.

36
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:48,210
That's when I realized I wasn't in
a tunnel at all.

37
00:02:51,964 --> 00:02:53,590
I was in a mine shaft.

38
00:02:55,843 --> 00:02:57,553
And if I kept going...

39
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:01,765
...there was only a dead end.

40
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:10,524
Then some man showed up
and offered me his hand.

41
00:03:11,483 --> 00:03:13,277
He helped me get out of there.

42
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:17,573
Everything was so bright.

43
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:22,119
I was blinded by him.
He was all I could see.

44
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:25,539
Funny, isn't it?

45
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:27,416
I thought I was different.

46
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,960
But I relied on a man
just like you.

47
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:34,006
All I ever wanted...

48
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:37,259
...was for your life
to turn out differently.

49
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,848
They say daughters
take after their mothers.

50
00:03:43,432 --> 00:03:44,683
Don't say that.

51
00:03:46,185 --> 00:03:47,895
That's exactly why...

52
00:03:49,438 --> 00:03:51,773
...I never wanted you
to call me Mom.

53
00:04:05,037 --> 00:04:06,914
Will you tell me what my father was like?

54
00:04:08,874 --> 00:04:10,042
Why?

55
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,960
You've never asked about him.

56
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:14,213
I know.

57
00:04:15,839 --> 00:04:17,341
I guess I'm just curious...

58
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:20,636
...now that I might never
have another chance to ask.

59
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,847
He was a poor man.

60
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,352
And you picked him?

61
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:30,521
I'm surprised.

62
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:32,814
I know.

63
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:38,403
Out of all those men I was with...

64
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:43,200
...he was the only one
I truly gave my heart to.

65
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,579
What?

66
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,581
Was he your first love?

67
00:04:53,836 --> 00:04:55,170
I guess.

68
00:04:57,381 --> 00:04:59,341
He was so handsome.

69
00:05:02,386 --> 00:05:04,221
One day when I was younger...

70
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:07,140
...there was a fight at work.

71
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,685
He showed up in his uniform.

72
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,771
He swept me into his arms
and saved me.

73
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:15,983
He just seemed so cool.

74
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:19,903
It felt like...

75
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:25,367
...that uniform would protect me forever.

76
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:33,250
So...

77
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:38,172
...what happened with
that man you mentioned?

78
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:42,467
It's over now.

79
00:05:43,594 --> 00:05:44,595
Why?

80
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:58,734
It's because of this.

81
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:03,280
What?

82
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:04,573
What is that?

83
00:06:05,115 --> 00:06:06,116
Mom.

84
00:06:06,617 --> 00:06:08,785
With something like this,

85
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:12,581
you can do anything you want to do
and avoid anything you don't want.

86
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:16,168
That's probably why people will do
whatever they can to get it.

87
00:06:19,463 --> 00:06:20,631
I did, too.

88
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:26,553
I was afraid to face someone I loved
and was grateful for...

89
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:29,223
...because I really thought...

90
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:31,683
...I thought he'd take it all from me.

91
00:06:34,186 --> 00:06:36,730
So I decided I'm going
to give him back half of it.

92
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,482
It was his in the first place.

93
00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:40,984
I know I'm selfish.

94
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:43,695
But maybe by doing this
I will finally be able

95
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:46,740
to find happiness in this life
just like I always wanted.

96
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:49,326
I have to try.

97
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:51,411
You...

98
00:06:53,497 --> 00:06:54,706
This is why.

99
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,420
This is why you've been acting so strange.

100
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,341
Even after seeing me...

101
00:07:05,968 --> 00:07:08,971
...you still don't know what happens
when greed takes over?

102
00:07:10,722 --> 00:07:14,977
Heeju, you never used
to be like this.

103
00:07:16,061 --> 00:07:18,480
I know that.
I know I've changed.

104
00:07:21,275 --> 00:07:23,110
Is that really such a bad thing?

105
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:27,197
If I'm nothing but bad luck
and I was never meant to have this

106
00:07:27,281 --> 00:07:28,991
and I just give it up,

107
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:31,118
what do you think's going
to happen to me then?

108
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:38,041
I'll just live Kim Heeju's old life
and die Yeo Sunok's death.

109
00:07:39,418 --> 00:07:41,503
Is that the kind
of future you want for me?

110
00:07:43,589 --> 00:07:45,215
Heeju.

111
00:07:46,258 --> 00:07:47,342
Don't worry, Mom.

112
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:49,178
I'll be outta here soon.

113
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,680
Just like you wanted, only...

114
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,433
...I want you to come with me, too.

115
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,351
Where are you going to go?

116
00:07:58,812 --> 00:07:59,897
Far away.

117
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,566
Somewhere very far.

118
00:08:07,863 --> 00:08:10,490
To a small French village up on
a mountaintop...

119
00:08:11,909 --> 00:08:14,036
...past endless fields of lavender.

120
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:17,623
It never smells like coal mines.

121
00:08:17,706 --> 00:08:20,209
It only smells like lavender
and clean air.

122
00:08:21,210 --> 00:08:23,545
Everyone there is happy and smiling.

123
00:08:24,588 --> 00:08:27,966
You and I can be like that, too,
if we go.

124
00:08:30,552 --> 00:08:31,637
Do you mean it?

125
00:08:34,223 --> 00:08:35,807
You're gonna take me with you?

126
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:39,937
Mm-hmm.

127
00:08:42,064 --> 00:08:43,106
Okay.

128
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,276
And if I die...

129
00:08:48,237 --> 00:08:50,989
...you can still go and scatter my ashes.

130
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:00,976
EPISODE 8
CHOICE

131
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:02,978
My father gave this
to me before he passed away.

132
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:04,062
Oh, really?

133
00:10:04,605 --> 00:10:07,065
Heh, still, who would
have thought the price

134
00:10:07,149 --> 00:10:08,775
of gold would get this high, right?

135
00:10:08,859 --> 00:10:12,237
So these gold bars,
your father left them to you?

136
00:10:14,573 --> 00:10:16,867
Yeah. Well, he only gave me two.

137
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:21,246
And about two weeks ago you came in to,
uh, sell the other gold bar?

138
00:10:21,663 --> 00:10:24,333
Your name is Kim Mincheol,
isn't it, sir?

139
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,168
That was me, yeah.

140
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:27,586
Please wait here a sec.

141
00:10:36,970 --> 00:10:37,971
Everything in order?

142
00:10:38,055 --> 00:10:39,056
-Yeah, it looks good.
-Good.

143
00:10:40,098 --> 00:10:42,100
Well, I'll see you again.

144
00:10:42,184 --> 00:10:43,352
Yeah.

145
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:45,270
-Thank you very much.
-Sure.

146
00:10:45,354 --> 00:10:46,730
-Thank you, sir.
-Yeah.

147
00:11:00,661 --> 00:11:02,371
Hello, President Ko.

148
00:11:02,454 --> 00:11:04,873
I'm calling from Lucky Jewelry
in Daejeong.

149
00:12:01,972 --> 00:12:04,725
Where on Earth are you headed now?

150
00:14:13,854 --> 00:14:15,564
Ah, shit.

151
00:15:02,861 --> 00:15:03,862
Hello, sir?

152
00:15:03,946 --> 00:15:05,364
Where the hell are you right now?

153
00:15:05,447 --> 00:15:07,824
Ju Haran's ID card, did you take it?

154
00:15:10,452 --> 00:15:12,204
What? Who?

155
00:15:12,955 --> 00:15:16,375
It's fucking chaos.
Ko has everyone looking for you.

156
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:18,627
Get your ass back here
before things get out of hand.

157
00:15:19,169 --> 00:15:21,630
Uh, I'm not sure what
you're talking about.

158
00:15:22,756 --> 00:15:24,758
And also, sir, I quit already.

159
00:15:25,884 --> 00:15:26,885
Woogy.

160
00:15:28,345 --> 00:15:29,513
I'm warning you.

161
00:15:30,389 --> 00:15:31,723
Uh, sir, but--

162
00:15:32,349 --> 00:15:34,309
Ah, shit.

163
00:15:34,685 --> 00:15:36,395
Fuck, I knew this would happen.

164
00:15:36,478 --> 00:15:38,230
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

165
00:15:44,653 --> 00:15:46,905
I'm fucked.
I'm fucked.

166
00:15:46,989 --> 00:15:48,907
Oh, shit, I'm so fucked.

167
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:51,034
How'd they know?

168
00:15:54,204 --> 00:15:55,622
Damn, this is crazy.

169
00:16:06,216 --> 00:16:07,384
Okay, okay.

170
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:09,887
This'll be more than enough. Yeah?

171
00:16:11,722 --> 00:16:13,473
What else can I do?

172
00:16:13,557 --> 00:16:15,267
Gotta save my own ass first.

173
00:16:20,063 --> 00:16:21,607
Right.

174
00:16:22,065 --> 00:16:23,317
I don't have a choice.

175
00:16:25,277 --> 00:16:27,821
Heeju, I'm sorry.

176
00:16:28,572 --> 00:16:29,907
I'm sorry.

177
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,825
Fuck, I don't know!

178
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:57,476
Stop the car!

179
00:16:59,144 --> 00:17:00,938
Kim Heeju!

180
00:17:01,021 --> 00:17:02,773
Stop the car and pull over!

181
00:17:05,943 --> 00:17:08,570
Kim Heeju!
Stop! I need to talk to you!

182
00:17:09,363 --> 00:17:10,489
I just need a minute!

183
00:17:10,572 --> 00:17:12,574
Please, just pull over!

184
00:17:32,719 --> 00:17:34,179
Ah, shit.

185
00:17:39,643 --> 00:17:41,144
Ms. Kim Heeju!

186
00:17:42,688 --> 00:17:46,441
Please step out of the car, yeah?
Don't you remember me?

187
00:17:46,525 --> 00:17:49,069
I'm a detective, Kim Jinman.
Don't you remember?

188
00:17:49,152 --> 00:17:50,779
I'm trying to help you!
You're in serious danger!

189
00:17:50,863 --> 00:17:51,864
Come on, step out!

190
00:17:52,364 --> 00:17:53,824
I'm not gonna hurt you!

191
00:17:59,037 --> 00:18:02,875
Finally.
Okay, do you have a plan?

192
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:04,293
You're in serious trouble.
You know that.

193
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:05,961
Right?

194
00:18:06,962 --> 00:18:08,255
Where are the gold bars?

195
00:18:09,047 --> 00:18:10,966
Are they in the car? Here?

196
00:18:29,735 --> 00:18:30,903
The gold bars, where were you--

197
00:18:37,743 --> 00:18:38,952
Is that a real gun?

198
00:18:39,036 --> 00:18:41,121
Is it?
Have you ever even fired it?

199
00:18:41,747 --> 00:18:42,915
Come on. Give it here.

200
00:18:45,375 --> 00:18:46,793
Close the trunk right now.

201
00:18:48,086 --> 00:18:49,338
The trunk! Close it!

202
00:18:59,723 --> 00:19:00,724
Kim Heeju.

203
00:19:00,807 --> 00:19:03,852
Listen, do you realize how serious
this situation is?

204
00:19:03,936 --> 00:19:07,064
Do you have any idea who you're dealing
with right now? Huh?

205
00:19:07,856 --> 00:19:09,775
The situation
is incredibly dangerous.

206
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,402
The Geumseong guys.
Yes Money.

207
00:19:12,945 --> 00:19:14,863
It's only a matter
of time before they track you down.

208
00:19:14,947 --> 00:19:16,240
And once they do, they'll kill you!

209
00:19:16,323 --> 00:19:17,866
- Do you get that?
- Of course I do.

210
00:19:18,492 --> 00:19:22,037
Do you? Really?
Why do this, huh?

211
00:19:22,621 --> 00:19:24,790
Those gold bars
don't belong to you!

212
00:19:24,873 --> 00:19:26,375
They belong to Chairman Ahn!

213
00:19:26,834 --> 00:19:28,877
You can live if you return the gold!

214
00:19:29,461 --> 00:19:30,963
If you're too scared
to give it back,

215
00:19:31,046 --> 00:19:32,172
I'll do it for you.

216
00:19:32,589 --> 00:19:34,049
Then you can leave the country!

217
00:19:34,132 --> 00:19:36,468
I'll help you get a passport
and anything else you need!

218
00:19:36,552 --> 00:19:37,845
Don't lie to me.

219
00:19:37,928 --> 00:19:40,722
What did Chairman Ahn promise you
for handing me over?

220
00:19:40,806 --> 00:19:43,141
Ah, you don't understand
a word I'm saying.

221
00:19:43,225 --> 00:19:44,393
Go!

222
00:19:45,018 --> 00:19:46,603
Just get outta here, please!

223
00:19:46,687 --> 00:19:48,313
If I was going to,

224
00:19:48,397 --> 00:19:50,774
I would have given the gold back
a long time ago!

225
00:19:51,275 --> 00:19:52,901
The gold bars
have completely blinded you

226
00:19:52,985 --> 00:19:54,111
and now you're not thinking straight!

227
00:19:54,194 --> 00:19:55,904
You've completely lost your mind!

228
00:19:56,488 --> 00:19:57,698
Just take a breath, okay?

229
00:19:57,781 --> 00:19:59,575
Let's try and be realistic here.

230
00:20:00,951 --> 00:20:03,161
You can't turn all the bars into cash.

231
00:20:03,245 --> 00:20:04,496
And even if you do,

232
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:06,957
you realize that's over
100 billion won, right?

233
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:09,168
How are you gonna spend all
that money before you die?

234
00:20:09,251 --> 00:20:10,419
Huh?

235
00:20:10,919 --> 00:20:12,713
If I return the gold
to Chairman Ahn,

236
00:20:12,796 --> 00:20:14,006
he promised to pay me!

237
00:20:14,548 --> 00:20:16,216
And I'll give all of it to you.

238
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:19,011
Then you get to live!

239
00:20:19,803 --> 00:20:21,555
You can go somewhere far away!

240
00:20:23,724 --> 00:20:24,808
Like France, huh?

241
00:20:24,892 --> 00:20:26,685
Take your mom
and go to France!

242
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:29,271
Sound like a plan? Yeah?

243
00:20:29,354 --> 00:20:30,939
Give me the gun.

244
00:20:34,026 --> 00:20:35,110
Don't you dare move!

245
00:20:38,697 --> 00:20:40,199
Don't follow me.

246
00:20:40,616 --> 00:20:42,201
Don't go looking for me.

247
00:20:42,284 --> 00:20:43,744
And you'd better leave my aunt alone, too!

248
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,208
Hey, Kim Heeju!

249
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:17,402
HEEJU

250
00:21:17,486 --> 00:21:19,029
Ah, dammit, seriously?

251
00:21:37,798 --> 00:21:39,299
HEEJU

252
00:21:41,468 --> 00:21:42,636
Hey, Heeju.

253
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:45,013
Detective Kim tailed me.

254
00:21:45,097 --> 00:21:46,890
He just pulled me over.

255
00:21:46,974 --> 00:21:49,518
And he saw the gold bars in my trunk, too.

256
00:21:49,601 --> 00:21:50,602
What?

257
00:21:50,686 --> 00:21:52,145
How did he know to follow you?

258
00:21:52,729 --> 00:21:54,606
I think he was staking out
the hospital.

259
00:21:54,690 --> 00:21:56,525
He had to be listening in.

260
00:21:57,651 --> 00:22:00,237
Somehow he knew everything I said
to my aunt there.

261
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,780
Wait. So then...

262
00:22:02,948 --> 00:22:06,577
...he has to know you're really Kim Heeju
and not Ju Haran.

263
00:22:08,078 --> 00:22:10,080
What about now?
Is he still tailing you?

264
00:22:10,163 --> 00:22:11,832
Uh, no. I'm okay.

265
00:22:12,416 --> 00:22:14,418
I threatened him with the gun and ran.

266
00:22:15,586 --> 00:22:17,004
Okay, good work.

267
00:22:17,087 --> 00:22:19,631
So anyway, now you better just
find somewhere to hide.

268
00:22:19,715 --> 00:22:20,716
And then...

269
00:22:21,592 --> 00:22:23,385
...well, I'll figure out what's going on
and call you.

270
00:22:23,468 --> 00:22:24,469
No.

271
00:22:24,970 --> 00:22:27,848
I don't have time for that.
Where are you now?

272
00:22:27,931 --> 00:22:29,892
Are you still at
the jewelry store?

273
00:22:30,517 --> 00:22:31,852
Did you get the cash yet?

274
00:22:31,935 --> 00:22:34,104
Uh, yeah.

275
00:22:35,022 --> 00:22:36,231
The jewelry store.

276
00:22:36,815 --> 00:22:38,150
I got the cash already.

277
00:22:39,109 --> 00:22:40,694
I'm gonna head that way now.

278
00:22:41,570 --> 00:22:42,779
I'll meet you there.

279
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:53,457
Ah!

280
00:22:57,669 --> 00:22:58,879
Dammit.

281
00:23:01,798 --> 00:23:03,759
Okay, let's just run.

282
00:23:04,718 --> 00:23:05,969
All right.

283
00:23:06,053 --> 00:23:07,888
Fuck it. Whatever.

284
00:23:09,223 --> 00:23:10,766
Yeah, fuck it.
I don't care.

285
00:23:12,643 --> 00:23:13,977
Ah, fuck.

286
00:23:25,113 --> 00:23:27,032
Hey, I'm almost there now.
What about you?

287
00:23:28,742 --> 00:23:29,993
Are you there yet?

288
00:23:30,077 --> 00:23:31,370
Yeah, I'm here already.

289
00:23:31,453 --> 00:23:33,372
You are?
I don't see you.

290
00:23:34,248 --> 00:23:35,958
Do you see me waving
at the end of the alley?

291
00:23:38,752 --> 00:23:41,922
Oh. Yeah, I see you.

292
00:23:42,589 --> 00:23:43,590
Is that your car?

293
00:23:44,299 --> 00:23:45,926
Here, over here.
You can park--

294
00:23:50,556 --> 00:23:51,932
Uh, hey, Heeju.

295
00:23:52,015 --> 00:23:53,851
I think the guys are here.
Open the window. The window.

296
00:23:53,934 --> 00:23:55,227
Hurry. Open it. The window.

297
00:23:56,645 --> 00:23:58,355
Hey, isn't that Woogy?

298
00:23:59,815 --> 00:24:01,233
The window. Just open it.

299
00:24:01,692 --> 00:24:02,693
The window?

300
00:24:07,197 --> 00:24:08,323
- Get him!
- Heeju!

301
00:24:08,407 --> 00:24:11,034
In my car! I got the gold bars
and the cash.

302
00:24:11,118 --> 00:24:12,452
Go get 'em!

303
00:24:12,536 --> 00:24:13,871
And then go hide somewhere! Hurry!

304
00:24:13,954 --> 00:24:15,080
- Hello?
- Hey!

305
00:24:15,163 --> 00:24:16,832
Shit!

306
00:24:16,915 --> 00:24:18,041
Woogy!

307
00:24:19,042 --> 00:24:21,003
Woogy? You there?

308
00:24:25,966 --> 00:24:26,967
Ah!

309
00:24:29,469 --> 00:24:31,972
Son of a bitch!
Woogy!

310
00:24:37,603 --> 00:24:40,189
Hey! Stop!

311
00:24:42,274 --> 00:24:44,109
- Guys, split up!
- This way.

312
00:24:44,193 --> 00:24:45,235
Come on!

313
00:24:46,028 --> 00:24:48,238
Hey! You motherfucker!

314
00:24:54,828 --> 00:24:57,456
What the fuck?
Go, go, go, go, go, go!

315
00:25:01,043 --> 00:25:02,044
Get him!

316
00:25:09,176 --> 00:25:10,177
Come on, man.
We're like brothers.

317
00:25:10,260 --> 00:25:12,387
- Let's go, Woogy.
- Can't we talk it out?

318
00:25:12,471 --> 00:25:14,723
Stay back!
I said stay back, for fuck's sake!

319
00:25:16,391 --> 00:25:17,643
Don't come any closer.

320
00:25:17,726 --> 00:25:19,561
Ah, fuck this shit!

321
00:25:20,812 --> 00:25:22,231
Shit, shit!

322
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:26,443
Shit, shit.

323
00:25:26,527 --> 00:25:28,153
Ah, fuck!

324
00:25:28,237 --> 00:25:29,571
He went that way!
Come on, let's go!

325
00:25:32,866 --> 00:25:34,159
Oh, shit.

326
00:25:41,542 --> 00:25:44,002
Ah, fuck's sake.

327
00:25:46,380 --> 00:25:47,756
Ah, shit.

328
00:26:06,859 --> 00:26:08,277
Woogy, open up!

329
00:26:09,778 --> 00:26:10,946
I'm gonna break it down!

330
00:26:11,572 --> 00:26:12,656
You hear me?

331
00:26:15,242 --> 00:26:17,119
Woogy!

332
00:26:27,713 --> 00:26:28,839
Woogy, hey.

333
00:26:29,214 --> 00:26:31,133
Heeju.

334
00:26:33,385 --> 00:26:35,429
What are you gonna do with that money?

335
00:26:35,512 --> 00:26:37,431
What are you talking about?

336
00:26:37,514 --> 00:26:39,016
Tell me where you are, please.

337
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:42,102
I've seen it happen over and over.

338
00:26:42,769 --> 00:26:43,896
Hey, Woogy!

339
00:26:44,479 --> 00:26:47,357
Stupid people who got greedy
and ruined their lives.

340
00:26:47,858 --> 00:26:49,610
My father was one of those guys.

341
00:26:49,693 --> 00:26:52,696
Open the door while
I'm asking nicely. 'Kay?

342
00:26:53,238 --> 00:26:55,490
And fuck me.
I guess I got greedy, too.

343
00:26:57,534 --> 00:26:59,620
I didn't even get
to spend all the money.

344
00:27:00,579 --> 00:27:02,247
Just tell me where you are right now.

345
00:27:02,915 --> 00:27:04,458
Did you get away from those guys?

346
00:27:05,542 --> 00:27:07,127
Hey, motherfucker!

347
00:27:07,211 --> 00:27:08,795
Just open the door!

348
00:27:08,879 --> 00:27:10,214
- Heeju.
- Huh?

349
00:27:11,715 --> 00:27:12,841
Open up!

350
00:27:14,593 --> 00:27:16,261
I won't last long at the farm, okay?

351
00:27:16,345 --> 00:27:18,430
- You son of a bitch!
- I'll give up your name.

352
00:27:19,890 --> 00:27:24,186
So as soon as we hang up,
you need to run as far as you can.

353
00:27:25,062 --> 00:27:26,355
You can take all the gold.

354
00:27:26,647 --> 00:27:28,273
- Break the door down.
- You'll find it in the trunk

355
00:27:28,357 --> 00:27:29,816
with the cash.
All of it is there.

356
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:30,984
Harder, you idiot!

357
00:27:31,068 --> 00:27:33,153
Take everything.
Take it and run.

358
00:27:33,237 --> 00:27:35,155
- Got it?
- Hey, you just--

359
00:27:35,239 --> 00:27:38,075
just make it as long as you can.
I'll--I'll be there right away.

360
00:27:38,659 --> 00:27:40,285
You know
what this reminds me of?

361
00:27:41,703 --> 00:27:43,247
When we used to play freeze tag.

362
00:27:45,999 --> 00:27:48,085
I got tagged in the mining town
and had to freeze.

363
00:27:48,168 --> 00:27:49,294
What are you doing?

364
00:27:49,795 --> 00:27:51,171
Try lifting it.

365
00:27:51,630 --> 00:27:53,674
I was so scared until you tagged me.

366
00:27:53,757 --> 00:27:54,800
Break the whole thing down!

367
00:27:56,301 --> 00:27:57,678
You really forgot all that?

368
00:28:00,722 --> 00:28:01,890
- Woogy--
- I gotta go.

369
00:28:01,974 --> 00:28:03,767
- Open it, fucker!
- Wait a minute.

370
00:28:03,851 --> 00:28:05,185
- Woogy? Hey!
- The fuck are you doing?

371
00:28:20,284 --> 00:28:21,285
Woogy.

372
00:28:21,952 --> 00:28:22,995
Let's go.

373
00:28:27,958 --> 00:28:29,501
Oh, what do I do?

374
00:28:45,225 --> 00:28:46,226
The gold bars are in the trunk.

375
00:28:47,561 --> 00:28:48,604
Heeju.

376
00:28:50,314 --> 00:28:53,025
I'll sell the gold bars
and I'll come right back.

377
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:56,403
Don't bother.

378
00:28:57,112 --> 00:28:59,281
This will be the last time
we see each other.

379
00:29:00,115 --> 00:29:01,867
You still have
Ju Haran's account, right?

380
00:29:02,618 --> 00:29:04,244
Once I get the cash for the gold,

381
00:29:04,328 --> 00:29:06,246
I'll wire the money back
to the bank account.

382
00:29:07,497 --> 00:29:09,041
What? Why?

383
00:29:09,124 --> 00:29:10,751
Because you don't trust me
right now.

384
00:29:12,503 --> 00:29:13,504
So...

385
00:29:14,421 --> 00:29:16,757
I wanna make sure you get your half first.

386
00:29:18,550 --> 00:29:21,011
You wanna break up because you're afraid
I'll take everything.

387
00:29:22,095 --> 00:29:23,096
But...

388
00:29:24,806 --> 00:29:27,392
...now that I have my share,
I know what matters.

389
00:29:28,435 --> 00:29:29,811
I can lose everything else.

390
00:29:30,646 --> 00:29:31,939
But I can't lose you, Heeju.

391
00:29:34,191 --> 00:29:35,317
Come on.

392
00:29:37,194 --> 00:29:39,446
Ah, what's happening here, huh?

393
00:29:40,906 --> 00:29:42,741
Is this the guy getting on
the ferry?

394
00:29:43,784 --> 00:29:44,785
Yeah.

395
00:29:45,786 --> 00:29:46,787
Oh.

396
00:29:47,704 --> 00:29:49,706
Pay up. Money.

397
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:50,916
- Come on. Money, money.
- Uh...

398
00:29:54,837 --> 00:29:55,838
You can check it.

399
00:30:04,555 --> 00:30:05,764
Let's go.

400
00:31:06,283 --> 00:31:12,915
HEEJU

401
00:31:15,667 --> 00:31:18,587
Come on. Please pick up the phone.

402
00:31:33,477 --> 00:31:34,853
Boss, over here.

403
00:31:35,646 --> 00:31:36,855
Where is he?

404
00:31:36,939 --> 00:31:38,398
He's that way. I'll show you.

405
00:31:39,149 --> 00:31:40,984
Hey bro! Hey!

406
00:31:41,068 --> 00:31:42,486
Let's go get this over with.

407
00:31:42,569 --> 00:31:43,654
Come on.

408
00:31:43,737 --> 00:31:45,572
Let's get outta here.

409
00:31:45,656 --> 00:31:47,032
It fuckin' reeks.

410
00:32:09,096 --> 00:32:10,889
Where's the gold?

411
00:32:13,308 --> 00:32:14,852
I--I don't know.

412
00:32:19,481 --> 00:32:21,483
I mean it. If I knew,
I woulda told the company.

413
00:32:22,943 --> 00:32:23,944
But that bitch...

414
00:32:26,196 --> 00:32:27,906
...she wouldn't tell me where
she hid the gold.

415
00:32:31,743 --> 00:32:33,412
I'm so sorry, Boss.

416
00:32:35,038 --> 00:32:36,498
I was blinded by the gold.

417
00:32:38,584 --> 00:32:40,419
She gave me these one-kilo bars.

418
00:32:40,502 --> 00:32:42,004
She asked me to sell them for her.

419
00:32:43,797 --> 00:32:45,591
Said I could keep one out of ten.

420
00:32:47,885 --> 00:32:48,969
Who is she?

421
00:32:51,180 --> 00:32:52,556
I don't know her name, sir.

422
00:32:52,639 --> 00:32:54,474
Do you think I'm fucking stupid?

423
00:32:59,438 --> 00:33:01,732
I really don't know.
I really don't. Please, I don't know.

424
00:33:01,815 --> 00:33:03,358
Boss, please, please!
Please, Boss! I don't--

425
00:33:05,444 --> 00:33:07,821
You were the one who took Ju Haran's ID
and passed it onto that bitch.

426
00:33:08,488 --> 00:33:10,073
I--I mean it, boss!
I really don't know her name! Please!

427
00:33:10,157 --> 00:33:11,867
Please, you gotta believe me!
I don't know anything! Please!

428
00:33:14,870 --> 00:33:18,040
She just told me to call her Boss.

429
00:33:27,216 --> 00:33:28,300
Fine, then.

430
00:33:31,386 --> 00:33:32,971
Choose from these pictures.

431
00:33:34,848 --> 00:33:36,433
No.

432
00:33:40,479 --> 00:33:43,106
N--no.

433
00:33:47,986 --> 00:33:49,154
No.

434
00:33:51,365 --> 00:33:52,699
It's not Kim Heeju?

435
00:33:53,951 --> 00:33:55,118
No.

436
00:33:59,581 --> 00:34:01,625
You told me you didn't know her name.

437
00:34:02,459 --> 00:34:03,961
How do you know it's not her?

438
00:34:06,046 --> 00:34:07,548
I...

439
00:34:09,675 --> 00:34:11,635
Fucker.

440
00:34:12,219 --> 00:34:13,345
No, sir, I real--
I really don't know!

441
00:34:21,770 --> 00:34:22,896
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

442
00:34:26,817 --> 00:34:28,068
Hey, Director Park.

443
00:34:28,151 --> 00:34:29,444
I looked into Kim Heeju.

444
00:34:29,862 --> 00:34:31,363
I texted you her background check.

445
00:34:31,947 --> 00:34:33,198
And I pulled her phone records.

446
00:34:33,699 --> 00:34:35,409
Looks like her phone
is currently off.

447
00:34:36,118 --> 00:34:38,579
There's no call activity
for the past few days, either.

448
00:34:39,496 --> 00:34:41,415
And then about a week ago,

449
00:34:41,498 --> 00:34:44,835
some of her phone's location pings
started matching Ju Haran's.

450
00:34:45,502 --> 00:34:46,503
Which ones?

451
00:34:47,504 --> 00:34:50,716
Gangwon Saebyeok Hospital
and Ilyeong Industrial Complex.

452
00:34:51,383 --> 00:34:52,676
Where's Ilyeong?

453
00:34:52,759 --> 00:34:56,221
Uh, yeah, you know, the area
along Route 6 with the warehouses.

454
00:34:56,305 --> 00:34:59,391
-The redevelopment area.
-Huh.

455
00:34:59,474 --> 00:35:03,729
And also on Bukju street in Jeongsan.
The Haengbok Pawnshop, too.

456
00:35:05,105 --> 00:35:06,815
Can you check out the industrial complex?

457
00:35:06,899 --> 00:35:08,233
Uh, yeah.

458
00:35:08,317 --> 00:35:09,318
I can do that.

459
00:35:11,278 --> 00:35:12,362
Gitae!

460
00:35:13,113 --> 00:35:14,114
Yes, Boss!

461
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:18,118
Send some of your guys over
to Haengbok Pawnshop on Bukju Street.

462
00:35:18,702 --> 00:35:19,786
I'll send you the pictures.

463
00:35:20,370 --> 00:35:21,830
Haengbok Pawnshop, sir?

464
00:35:22,289 --> 00:35:24,499
Actually, you should go yourself.

465
00:35:24,583 --> 00:35:25,584
Yes, sir.

466
00:35:32,382 --> 00:35:34,676
Hey, Mister Jin.
Can you take care of some meat?

467
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:36,970
I'm in the barn.
The operating room.

468
00:35:39,556 --> 00:35:40,974
No, he's still alive.

469
00:35:44,019 --> 00:35:45,604
Yeah, cutting up and butchering.

470
00:35:47,272 --> 00:35:49,191
You can do whatever you want
with the organs.

471
00:35:49,274 --> 00:35:50,943
Please don't kill me.

472
00:35:54,446 --> 00:35:56,198
Here, here, here, here, here.
I think that's the one.

473
00:35:56,657 --> 00:35:57,824
-Yeah, that looks like it.
-Stop here.

474
00:35:57,908 --> 00:36:00,744
-Haengbok.
-Yeah. Okay.

475
00:36:12,214 --> 00:36:15,634
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

476
00:36:47,457 --> 00:36:49,918
We just rent out the space here.
That's all.

477
00:36:50,752 --> 00:36:52,754
We don't check what they're using it for.

478
00:37:09,521 --> 00:37:10,814
They do something bad?

479
00:37:10,898 --> 00:37:12,107
No, nothin' big.

480
00:37:12,191 --> 00:37:13,233
Just a petty crime.

481
00:37:14,026 --> 00:37:15,235
If they come back here...

482
00:37:16,403 --> 00:37:17,487
...be sure to call me right away.

483
00:37:17,571 --> 00:37:18,655
GANGWON CENTRAL POLICE AGENCY
INVESTIGATIONS DIVISION

484
00:37:18,739 --> 00:37:19,823
DETECTIVE KANG DONGHOON

485
00:37:20,782 --> 00:37:21,783
Uh-huh.

486
00:37:34,963 --> 00:37:37,007
In 100 meters, turn left.

487
00:38:28,058 --> 00:38:29,685
Don't fight it.

488
00:38:30,185 --> 00:38:32,604
Just let yourself pass out.

489
00:38:33,564 --> 00:38:36,316
If you don't,
it'll be a lot worse.

490
00:39:00,340 --> 00:39:03,343
CLOSING MINES WITHOUT A PLAN
MEANS NO LIVELIHOOD FOR RESIDENTS!

491
00:39:09,016 --> 00:39:11,101
- Wait up!
- Freeze!

492
00:39:11,185 --> 00:39:12,186
Ah!

493
00:39:13,979 --> 00:39:15,522
Ah! Freeze!

494
00:39:16,356 --> 00:39:17,608
Tag!

495
00:39:17,691 --> 00:39:18,901
Gonna get you!

496
00:39:20,319 --> 00:39:22,112
Freeze!

497
00:39:25,824 --> 00:39:27,117
Come here!

498
00:39:28,869 --> 00:39:30,787
Stop it!
Get away from me!

499
00:39:31,580 --> 00:39:34,082
Hyewon. That's enough.

500
00:39:34,166 --> 00:39:36,919
Dinner's ready.
Your food's getting cold.

501
00:39:37,002 --> 00:39:40,005
Minu, let's go home!
Come on. It's time for dinner.

502
00:39:41,340 --> 00:39:44,176
I can't believe this.
You little rascal.

503
00:39:44,259 --> 00:39:46,887
Where have you been?
I was worried sick!

504
00:39:48,764 --> 00:39:50,182
Mongsil!

505
00:40:04,238 --> 00:40:05,614
Why are you here by yourself?

506
00:40:06,156 --> 00:40:07,658
'Cause I'm frozen here.

507
00:40:08,075 --> 00:40:09,409
Everybody else went home.

508
00:40:09,493 --> 00:40:10,702
You better go, too.

509
00:40:11,161 --> 00:40:13,038
I can't until I get tagged.

510
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:15,040
You're a dummy.

511
00:40:15,123 --> 00:40:16,792
That means you'll be here all night.

512
00:40:16,875 --> 00:40:18,085
There are ghosts here.

513
00:40:20,712 --> 00:40:21,922
Tag me free.

514
00:40:23,048 --> 00:40:24,049
You do it!

515
00:40:24,842 --> 00:40:26,260
You tag me!

516
00:40:58,250 --> 00:40:59,293
Woogy!

517
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:10,012
Woogy?

518
00:41:10,304 --> 00:41:11,346
Heeju?

519
00:41:13,307 --> 00:41:14,558
Heeju.

520
00:41:22,608 --> 00:41:23,775
Is this it?

521
00:41:24,193 --> 00:41:26,695
Okay. Okay. Okay.

522
00:41:26,778 --> 00:41:28,030
You find the key?

523
00:41:28,113 --> 00:41:30,115
- Oh! It worked! Yes.
- You got it? You got it?

524
00:41:31,742 --> 00:41:32,993
What--how do I...

525
00:41:33,660 --> 00:41:35,537
Hey. There.

526
00:41:35,621 --> 00:41:36,788
Shoot.

527
00:41:37,414 --> 00:41:38,749
There.

528
00:41:41,084 --> 00:41:42,753
There, there, there. Shoot. Shoot.

529
00:41:42,836 --> 00:41:45,297
Kill him. There. There.

530
00:42:27,631 --> 00:42:29,341
KIM HEEJU
NO PATIENTS MATCH THE SEARCH CRITERIA.

531
00:42:32,553 --> 00:42:35,556
We don't have anyone named Kim Heeju here.

532
00:42:36,056 --> 00:42:37,307
Ju Haran, then.

533
00:42:38,183 --> 00:42:39,726
Ju Haran.

534
00:42:42,563 --> 00:42:43,814
I'm sorry.

535
00:42:45,816 --> 00:42:47,317
A guardian, maybe?

536
00:42:47,401 --> 00:42:48,819
What about a guardian?

537
00:42:49,611 --> 00:42:51,238
Kim Heeju or Ju Haran.

538
00:43:10,674 --> 00:43:12,467
What?

539
00:43:12,551 --> 00:43:13,927
What now?

540
00:43:21,268 --> 00:43:22,436
What?

541
00:43:26,773 --> 00:43:28,108
Ah, shit.

542
00:44:09,399 --> 00:44:13,362
CALLS

543
00:44:16,073 --> 00:44:18,200
HEEJU

544
00:44:19,076 --> 00:44:22,120
Your call has been forwarded
to an automated voice messaging system.

545
00:44:22,204 --> 00:44:24,039
The number you have dial--

546
00:44:33,423 --> 00:44:35,050
KIM HEEJU

547
00:44:36,844 --> 00:44:39,221
Where are we?

548
00:44:39,888 --> 00:44:42,140
Huh? Not the pawnshop, right?

549
00:44:42,641 --> 00:44:43,642
We can't go there.

550
00:44:44,226 --> 00:44:45,352
I know.

551
00:44:46,979 --> 00:44:49,064
I was on the way to the workshop.

552
00:44:49,398 --> 00:44:50,691
But then the car broke down.

553
00:44:57,322 --> 00:44:58,323
Heeju.

554
00:45:01,577 --> 00:45:02,786
We're fucked.

555
00:45:04,246 --> 00:45:05,581
Park knows about you.

556
00:45:06,790 --> 00:45:07,875
He knows you're Ju Haran.

557
00:45:09,418 --> 00:45:11,461
I even held out till the very end.

558
00:45:12,045 --> 00:45:13,088
Fuck.

559
00:45:19,720 --> 00:45:21,471
INCOMING CALL
AUNTIE SUNOK

560
00:45:24,808 --> 00:45:26,018
What? Something wrong?

561
00:45:27,603 --> 00:45:30,272
Aunt Sunok has never called me
on this number.

562
00:45:33,192 --> 00:45:35,986
INCOMING CALL
AUNTIE SUNOK

563
00:45:40,282 --> 00:45:43,869
Am I speaking
with Ms. Yeo Sunok's guardian?

564
00:45:44,536 --> 00:45:45,537
Who are you?

565
00:45:47,623 --> 00:45:49,166
I'm Yeo Sunok's doctor.

566
00:45:49,416 --> 00:45:50,959
I'm in charge of her care.

567
00:45:51,877 --> 00:45:53,253
Your mother
is in critical condition.

568
00:45:53,337 --> 00:45:54,880
You need to come
to the hospital right away.

569
00:45:55,923 --> 00:45:58,800
I'm using this phone since we didn't
have your number, Ms. Kim Heeju.

570
00:46:00,302 --> 00:46:02,554
Oh, my mistake.

571
00:46:02,638 --> 00:46:03,931
Ju Haran.

572
00:46:17,528 --> 00:46:19,363
My aunt.
Someone's in her hospital room.

573
00:46:19,696 --> 00:46:20,697
Huh?

574
00:46:25,869 --> 00:46:27,538
Saebaek Hospital, oncology ward.

575
00:46:27,955 --> 00:46:29,790
Hi, this is Ms. Yeo Sunok's guardian.

576
00:46:29,873 --> 00:46:32,000
Can--can you send someone
to check on her, please?

577
00:46:32,084 --> 00:46:35,963
It seems someone's--there's--there's
someone strange in her room right now.

578
00:48:56,353 --> 00:48:57,354
Hello?

579
00:48:58,105 --> 00:48:59,523
Where are you, Detective Kim?

580
00:49:02,609 --> 00:49:04,361
Uh, I'm at the office right now.

581
00:49:04,736 --> 00:49:06,780
It's a busy night
so I'm doing some overtime.

582
00:49:08,866 --> 00:49:09,867
Really?

583
00:49:10,617 --> 00:49:14,329
So that gray SUV I see,
that's not your car?

584
00:49:14,955 --> 00:49:17,082
Why'd you ask me
if you knew where I was?

585
00:49:22,212 --> 00:49:23,672
How long have you been following me?

586
00:49:24,214 --> 00:49:25,507
Since the hospital.

587
00:49:26,049 --> 00:49:27,050
Mm.

588
00:49:29,928 --> 00:49:32,347
Tell me. How much do you know, then?

589
00:49:32,973 --> 00:49:33,974
Ju Haran?

590
00:49:34,850 --> 00:49:37,269
Ju Haran is a person you took care
of long ago.

591
00:49:38,645 --> 00:49:41,064
As soon as I gave you all her information
she went missing.

592
00:49:42,774 --> 00:49:43,859
Hmm.

593
00:49:44,902 --> 00:49:45,986
I remember.

594
00:49:47,696 --> 00:49:48,697
What about...

595
00:49:49,364 --> 00:49:50,365
...Kim Heeju?

596
00:49:56,496 --> 00:49:58,665
You really know how
to sniff things out.

597
00:49:59,875 --> 00:50:03,045
You're like a fucking dog, Detective Kim.

598
00:50:05,881 --> 00:50:07,007
What are you talking about?

599
00:50:07,549 --> 00:50:08,550
Huh?

600
00:50:08,884 --> 00:50:10,093
Kim Heeju? Who's that?

601
00:50:11,970 --> 00:50:14,848
Ah. Yeah. Yangpo Airport.

602
00:50:14,932 --> 00:50:16,266
She's on the security team.

603
00:50:16,600 --> 00:50:18,644
Have you told Chairman
Ahn about Kim Heeju?

604
00:50:19,353 --> 00:50:22,272
You're here all by yourself,
so I bet you haven't, right?

605
00:50:24,024 --> 00:50:25,025
Well, then.

606
00:50:26,652 --> 00:50:27,903
That means we have the same goal.

607
00:50:28,695 --> 00:50:29,988
What the hell are you saying?

608
00:50:30,697 --> 00:50:33,450
I just do what I'm told, Park.
You should already know that.

609
00:50:34,493 --> 00:50:36,787
The Chairman told me to find you
so that's what I'm doing.

610
00:50:37,454 --> 00:50:40,791
Whoever gets to Kim Heeju first gets all
the gold. Right?

611
00:50:41,834 --> 00:50:45,170
And the two of us are the only ones
who know that Kim Heeju has the gold.

612
00:50:47,798 --> 00:50:49,216
Park, listen.

613
00:50:49,675 --> 00:50:52,511
I couldn't care less about who takes
the gold bars.

614
00:50:52,594 --> 00:50:54,263
I really don't give a shit.

615
00:50:54,346 --> 00:50:55,848
So one of us has to fucking die!

616
00:51:52,988 --> 00:51:55,782
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

617
00:52:06,418 --> 00:52:07,711
Geez, what happened to you?

618
00:52:07,794 --> 00:52:11,381
Huh? Oh, you're here.
Help me up. Shit.

619
00:52:13,383 --> 00:52:14,801
Fuck me.

620
00:52:17,679 --> 00:52:19,640
Look at me.
I almost died.

621
00:52:21,058 --> 00:52:22,309
What happened?

622
00:52:23,143 --> 00:52:24,978
Park, that fucking piece of shit,

623
00:52:25,062 --> 00:52:28,398
threatened to kill me and then he just
straight up rammed me with his car.

624
00:52:28,482 --> 00:52:29,650
- Dammit.
- What?

625
00:52:30,567 --> 00:52:32,236
Hey, by the way.

626
00:52:32,819 --> 00:52:34,404
What did you find out?

627
00:52:34,905 --> 00:52:37,366
You're the one who told Park about
the hospital.

628
00:52:37,449 --> 00:52:41,912
Yeah. He said it would settle
my Geumseong debts.

629
00:52:50,045 --> 00:52:51,380
Listen.

630
00:52:51,463 --> 00:52:52,840
Once Park finds her...

631
00:52:53,966 --> 00:52:55,717
...Ju Haran is a dead woman.

632
00:52:56,677 --> 00:52:58,804
It doesn't matter if she has
the casket or not.

633
00:52:59,596 --> 00:53:01,723
He's gonna kill her either way.

634
00:53:02,641 --> 00:53:05,269
If you knew about that
and still helped Park find her...

635
00:53:07,104 --> 00:53:08,605
...then you shouldn't be a police officer.

636
00:53:09,898 --> 00:53:11,567
You're just an asshole.

637
00:53:12,067 --> 00:53:13,861
Park has no ties
to Geumseong anymore.

638
00:53:13,944 --> 00:53:15,279
He can't settle your debt.

639
00:53:15,904 --> 00:53:19,241
He's just doing whatever it takes
to find the casket and then get out.

640
00:53:23,996 --> 00:53:26,665
You know he killed Cheon, right?

641
00:53:28,166 --> 00:53:29,251
Chairman Ahn wants Park dead.

642
00:53:29,334 --> 00:53:32,129
And that's why his men are crawling
all over Jeongsan right now.

643
00:53:32,838 --> 00:53:33,839
Did you know that?

644
00:53:35,632 --> 00:53:37,009
I kinda knew, yeah.

645
00:53:37,092 --> 00:53:38,927
And you still said yes?

646
00:53:39,011 --> 00:53:40,137
Huh?

647
00:53:40,220 --> 00:53:42,389
Chairman Ahn is gonna catch Park soon,

648
00:53:42,472 --> 00:53:44,766
and when he does we both know
what's gonna happen.

649
00:53:46,476 --> 00:53:49,104
You think a dead man
can help settle your debt?

650
00:53:50,314 --> 00:53:51,315
How much was it?

651
00:53:52,107 --> 00:53:53,233
Around 100 million won?

652
00:53:54,067 --> 00:53:55,360
If I bring back the gold...

653
00:53:55,986 --> 00:53:57,529
...the Chairman's promised to pay me.

654
00:53:57,613 --> 00:53:59,281
I can settle your debt.

655
00:53:59,781 --> 00:54:00,949
Do you mean that?

656
00:54:01,033 --> 00:54:02,034
Want it in writing?

657
00:54:05,412 --> 00:54:07,623
Wh--What am I supposed to tell Park?

658
00:54:07,706 --> 00:54:11,460
Just tell Park you're still looking
or something, 'kay?

659
00:54:12,044 --> 00:54:14,379
You just need to keep it vague, yeah?

660
00:54:15,255 --> 00:54:17,883
Hold him off until I get the casket back
to Chairman Ahn.

661
00:54:18,675 --> 00:54:21,845
Say whatever you need
to string him along, yeah?

662
00:54:22,137 --> 00:54:23,597
That son of a bitch Park...

663
00:54:24,431 --> 00:54:26,892
...he's definitely gonna die soon, got it?

664
00:54:27,559 --> 00:54:29,102
So you think this through.

665
00:54:31,522 --> 00:54:32,523
Okay.

666
00:54:54,503 --> 00:54:57,506
You're Yes Money guys, huh?

667
00:54:58,507 --> 00:54:59,508
Why are you here?

668
00:55:01,134 --> 00:55:02,803
Well, it's a hospital, you know?

669
00:55:02,886 --> 00:55:04,596
We're all here to see the doctor.

670
00:55:05,514 --> 00:55:07,140
This is the oncology ward.

671
00:55:08,141 --> 00:55:09,351
You have cancer?

672
00:55:09,434 --> 00:55:10,894
Yeah.

673
00:55:11,937 --> 00:55:14,106
Oh, really? All of them, too?

674
00:55:16,024 --> 00:55:18,527
Yeah.

675
00:55:19,319 --> 00:55:21,780
Give this message to Ko, 'kay?

676
00:55:22,906 --> 00:55:25,617
You have until the end of the day
to get all of your men outta here.

677
00:55:26,785 --> 00:55:30,622
Or I'll have to take everyone in
for obstruction of business. Got it?

678
00:55:34,918 --> 00:55:35,919
Here?

679
00:55:54,271 --> 00:55:55,314
What?

680
00:56:10,412 --> 00:56:11,830
Yeah, I got rid of it.

681
00:56:12,706 --> 00:56:13,916
What about the detective?

682
00:56:13,999 --> 00:56:15,834
I told you.
He's not here.

683
00:56:18,420 --> 00:56:19,838
I'll be there soon, okay?

684
00:56:20,881 --> 00:56:22,174
Can you stay with her?

685
00:56:22,257 --> 00:56:23,967
At least until I get there?

686
00:56:24,051 --> 00:56:25,469
Okay.

687
00:56:27,554 --> 00:56:29,806
Are you really gonna move her
somewhere else?

688
00:56:29,890 --> 00:56:32,851
Do we have to?
She's still unconscious.

689
00:56:32,935 --> 00:56:36,438
We got rid of the bug
so why not just keep her here?

690
00:56:36,522 --> 00:56:38,357
Won't the detective find her anyway?

691
00:56:38,440 --> 00:56:39,816
We can talk when I'm there.

692
00:56:39,900 --> 00:56:41,401
Fine.

693
00:56:48,033 --> 00:56:49,034
Hey.

694
00:56:49,576 --> 00:56:51,286
Just go to a doctor.

695
00:56:51,370 --> 00:56:52,496
Why would I do that?

696
00:56:55,457 --> 00:56:57,084
Just go.

697
00:57:10,931 --> 00:57:13,225
Excuse me?

698
00:57:13,308 --> 00:57:15,227
Will you call Kim Heeju
and let her know I'm here?

699
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:18,856
I need to talk to her.
Ask her to call me.

700
00:57:19,773 --> 00:57:22,317
K--Kim Heeju?

701
00:57:22,401 --> 00:57:25,529
I don't know anyone by that name.

702
00:57:26,238 --> 00:57:28,490
I don't have her number, either.

703
00:57:29,241 --> 00:57:30,450
Mija.

704
00:57:31,493 --> 00:57:32,786
You really don't recognize me?

705
00:57:33,704 --> 00:57:35,539
I was stationed at Jeongsan.

706
00:57:35,622 --> 00:57:37,749
Kim Jinman.
I was a constable then.

707
00:57:40,127 --> 00:57:42,129
Well, it's been 30 years,
I guess.

708
00:57:43,422 --> 00:57:44,548
Don't you remember?

709
00:57:45,424 --> 00:57:47,843
Sunok and I lived together
for around a year.

710
00:57:47,926 --> 00:57:48,927
Uh...

711
00:57:50,012 --> 00:57:51,180
You remember me, right?

712
00:58:12,492 --> 00:58:14,453
- Yeah, Aunt Mija?
- Heeju.

713
00:58:14,536 --> 00:58:17,289
- Detective Kim is here right now.
-What?

714
00:58:27,758 --> 00:58:29,051
Here you go.

715
00:58:29,134 --> 00:58:30,886
Heeju. There.

716
00:58:44,066 --> 00:58:45,067
Kim Heeju?

717
00:58:46,485 --> 00:58:48,237
It's Detective Kim Jinman.

718
00:58:49,112 --> 00:58:50,364
All right, then.

719
00:58:51,031 --> 00:58:53,367
You need to listen to me very carefully,
okay?

720
00:58:54,117 --> 00:58:57,079
Obviously, I know you have the casket.
And so does Park.

721
00:58:59,748 --> 00:59:02,626
You need to stay away from the hospital.

722
00:59:03,418 --> 00:59:06,296
I've got everything covered here
so don't worry about that.

723
00:59:08,298 --> 00:59:09,424
Listen, Kim Heeju.

724
00:59:12,052 --> 00:59:13,053
Park and I...

725
00:59:13,929 --> 00:59:17,558
...we're--we're really different, okay?

726
00:59:18,725 --> 00:59:21,520
Park is the kind of person who will stop
at nothing to find you.

727
00:59:22,354 --> 00:59:24,773
He's so much more evil
than anyone could even imagine.

728
00:59:24,857 --> 00:59:26,358
I really mean it, Heeju.

729
00:59:27,359 --> 00:59:29,611
You need to stop wasting time.

730
00:59:31,071 --> 00:59:33,991
Stop dragging this out and just tell
me where the casket is, Heeju.

731
00:59:35,284 --> 00:59:38,036
We need to return that thing
to Chairman Ahn.

732
00:59:38,120 --> 00:59:39,371
Today.

733
00:59:41,331 --> 00:59:44,543
If you don't, Chairman Ahn
and Park Hocheol won't leave you alone.

734
00:59:45,127 --> 00:59:47,921
I'm telling you they won't ever
stop looking for you.

735
00:59:48,005 --> 00:59:50,215
Okay? Do you understand?

736
00:59:56,680 --> 00:59:58,265
Hey.

737
01:00:15,407 --> 01:00:16,408
Hey.

738
01:00:18,660 --> 01:00:19,828
Sunok.

739
01:00:21,747 --> 01:00:22,873
Yeo Sunok.

740
01:00:27,419 --> 01:00:29,046
I'll save your daughter, okay?

741
01:00:34,843 --> 01:00:36,929
So don't worry.
Just rest up.

742
01:00:37,054 --> 01:00:40,307
Shit.

743
01:00:40,390 --> 01:00:41,391
Heeju.

744
01:00:44,770 --> 01:00:46,104
Should we do what he says?

745
01:00:48,565 --> 01:00:50,567
Should we just give
the chairman back his gold?

746
01:00:51,860 --> 01:00:53,028
He might be right.

747
01:00:53,987 --> 01:00:55,280
Maybe we should hand it all over.

748
01:00:55,656 --> 01:00:57,282
Before he finds out it's you.

749
01:00:58,075 --> 01:00:59,535
I think it'd be better that way.

750
01:01:02,454 --> 01:01:03,455
Heeju.

751
01:01:04,373 --> 01:01:05,916
You saw it yesterday.

752
01:01:07,417 --> 01:01:08,460
If they catch you...

753
01:01:09,837 --> 01:01:11,755
...the things they do
will be worse than death.

754
01:01:11,839 --> 01:01:15,050
Even if Detective Kim is really planning
to return the gold to Ahn,

755
01:01:15,133 --> 01:01:16,385
it's too late now.

756
01:01:17,177 --> 01:01:18,679
I gave half to Lee Dokyung.

757
01:01:19,388 --> 01:01:21,056
It's not possible to return it.

758
01:01:42,286 --> 01:01:43,829
And besides.

759
01:01:46,206 --> 01:01:49,585
Do you really think you can give up
the gold now?

760
01:01:49,668 --> 01:01:53,213
Just return it and go back
to the way things were before?

761
01:02:01,138 --> 01:02:02,264
I know I can't.

762
01:02:59,279 --> 01:03:03,909
♪ Another day another hour ♪

763
01:03:03,992 --> 01:03:08,288
♪ Free falling in my mind ♪

764
01:03:08,372 --> 01:03:15,379
♪ I will find all of the reasons
for leaving ♪

765
01:03:17,714 --> 01:03:22,803
♪ When everyone around me's changing ♪

766
01:03:22,886 --> 01:03:27,266
♪ Everyone but me ♪

767
01:03:27,349 --> 01:03:31,687
♪ All the things I thought I could be ♪

768
01:03:32,771 --> 01:03:35,232
♪ Are out of reach ♪

769
01:03:37,150 --> 01:03:41,738
♪ I leave it all behind ♪

770
01:03:41,822 --> 01:03:45,784
♪ As you fall in line ♪

771
01:03:45,868 --> 01:03:50,372
♪ I'm not expecting any light
at your door ♪

772
01:03:50,455 --> 01:03:52,124
♪ There's nothing left ♪

773
01:03:52,207 --> 01:03:58,463
♪ Just the pieces of everything
we could have been before ♪

774
01:03:58,547 --> 01:04:02,759
♪ Evermore ♪

775
01:04:02,843 --> 01:04:08,682
♪ I don't feel it like I used to ♪

776
01:04:08,765 --> 01:04:11,018
♪ Anymore ♪

777
01:04:23,655 --> 01:04:28,243
♪ You could find me in the dark ♪

778
01:04:28,327 --> 01:04:32,539
♪ Still calling through the night ♪

779
01:04:32,623 --> 01:04:37,503
♪ I leave behind all of the seasons ♪

780
01:04:37,586 --> 01:04:40,255
♪ I've dreamed of ♪

781
01:04:42,633 --> 01:04:49,556
♪ But the water's rising over
everything I've known ♪

782
01:04:49,640 --> 01:04:55,646
♪ Drifting out here all alone ♪

783
01:04:57,272 --> 01:05:01,360
♪ On your own ♪

784
01:05:01,443 --> 01:05:05,989
♪ So leave it all behind ♪

785
01:05:06,073 --> 01:05:10,452
♪ As you fall in line ♪

786
01:05:10,536 --> 01:05:12,371
♪ I'm not expect... ♪
